body:
@eric-haibin-lin @cjolivier01 what's the current agreement for this? I do not mind merging it after 1.0.1 release. Regarding whether we need to merge together with the changes which depends on this, I would prefer merging this first, because 

1.  it has been tested with ps-lite tests for core functionality (actually also tested with Spark in my own environment) and this change should not bring influences to the existing functionalities in mxnet

2. the other changes like Spark integration has their own focuses, I do not want to mix them with the mxnet changes here. It would bring some conveniences, for example, even if the changes here has some expected issue influencing other functionalities , it would be reverted easily; it will not block the merging of other updates in ps-lite if any

@szha Thank you! 

Yes, the change will overwrite the idx2name. I think it is unnecessary to provide the idx2name for user if the idx2name for the optimizer is the same as the idx2name in the mxnet.module.BaseModule. 

On what condition will the user need provide the idx2name for the optimizer instance? It is complicated to get the mapping from the index to the name of parameters.

@mseeger No, I don't know for sure this issue caused the hanging tests as I never saw one hang. Both issues being in laop3 felt too specific for coincidence so I assumed they were the same underlying problem. 

@szha Could be. Since the issue seems to be resolved now, it would just be testing that it wasn't broken at that point. 

Anyone know if we're still seeing the hanging issue in CI builds?

@piiswrong Could you please elaborate on that? 
1. Are you saying you don't want tutorials on symbolic interface and Gluon on the same page? 
2. Are you saying the way it is structured now is better? If not, how do you propose to restructure?

These changes were already accepted as part of the v1.0.0 release, but for "reasons" they're not showing up on the website. [See the file in v1 here](https://github.com/apache/incubator-mxnet/blob/v1.0.0/docs/tutorials/index.md). We need to sync things up.
I plan to build on top of this version by adding the recently fixed tutorials, so let's pass this one and begin iterating on it. 
@piiswrong if you have specific suggestions, I'll be happy to incorporate your feedback moving forward for subsequent versions.

@piiswrong 

While I agree there is a lot of work that needs to be done for the tutorials, we need to take incremental steps towards better contents organised better.

Dividing MXNet tutorials page into (1) Gluon and (2) MXNet gives the impression that Gluon and MXNet are separate things. Dividing a page on X into Y and X is illogical for any given X and Y. It is like dividing a page on Gluon tutorials into (1) RNN with Gluon (2) Gluon. I don't see how the existing organization is better; I think the existing organization is embarrassing for the reason stated above.

@zhreshold @piiswrong @szha 
I combined warmup and multi step scheduler in #8005.
Now, need I separate them?
